Package de.elo.ix.client.subs

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CheckinSubstitutionsInfo
    Object to define substitutions to be checked in.
    CheckoutSubstitutionsInfo
    This object is used to define which substitutions should be returned by IXServicePortIF.checkoutSubstitutions(de.elo.ix.client.ClientInfo, de.elo.ix.client.subs.CheckoutSubstitutionsInfo, de.elo.ix.client.subs.SubstitutionZ, de.elo.ix.client.LockZ).
    CreateSuperiorSubstitutionInfo
    Define how a superior substitution is created.
    DeleteSubstitutionsInfo
    Define which substitutions should be deleted.
    ForwardSubstitutionInfo
    Forward a substitution from the its current substitute to a new substitute.
    Substitution
    A Substitution is used to create, update and read substitutions.
    SubstitutionC
    Bit constants for members of Substitution
    SubstitutionDataC
    Bit constants which mirror the database classes.
    SubstitutionPeriod
    A substitution period is used to define time periods for substitutions.
    SubstitutionSettings
    This class wraps various boolean settings and parameters for Substitution
    SubstitutionsResult
    Object returned by IXServicePortIF.checkinSubstitutions(de.elo.ix.client.ClientInfo, de.elo.ix.client.subs.CheckinSubstitutionsInfo, de.elo.ix.client.subs.SubstitutionZ, de.elo.ix.client.LockZ)() and IXServicePortIF.checkoutSubstitutions(de.elo.ix.client.ClientInfo, de.elo.ix.client.subs.CheckoutSubstitutionsInfo, de.elo.ix.client.subs.SubstitutionZ, de.elo.ix.client.LockZ)().
    SubstitutionZ
    This class encapsulates the constants of SubstitutionC
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    SubstitutionStatus
    The substitution status is used to inform if a substitution is currently deactivated or activated.
